5.1 Creating Basic Charts
Charts help visualize data and identify trends:
  •	Bar/Column Charts: Ideal for comparing values across categories.
  •	Line Charts: Used for showing trends over time.
  •	Pie Charts: Used for showing proportions of a whole.

To create a chart:
  •	Select the data range.
  •	Click Insert and choose the type of chart from the Charts group.

5.2 Customizing Charts
After creating a chart, you can:
  •	Add Chart Titles, Axis Titles, and Legends using the Chart Tools.
  •	Change chart colors, labels, and data points for better clarity.
